<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFADFFC7D4CCF8960F7AFEF6" blockId="80.[151,1437,1853,2025]" lastBlockId="81.[151,1437,151,1618]" lastPageId="81" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D4CCF8960C1AF8C4" bold="true" box="[199,322,1853,1879]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFADFFC6D5BBF8950FD7F8CB" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[432,655,1854,1880]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzmarinae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D5BBF8950FD7F8CB" box="[432,655,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Tenedos luzmarinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D69EF8950F8CF8CB" bold="true" box="[661,724,1854,1880]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFADFFC6D69EF8950F8CF8CB" box="[661,724,1854,1880]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFADFFC6D7AEF8940871F8CB" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[933,1321,1854,1880]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peckorum">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D7AEF8940975F8CB" box="[933,1069,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">T. peckorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFADFFC6D03FF8950871F8CB" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[1076,1321,1854,1880]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFADFFC6D13FF89408C4F8CB" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[1332,1436,1854,1880]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quipile" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D13FF89408C4F8CB" box="[1332,1436,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">T. quipile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D49CF8C90D80F8EF" bold="true" box="[151,216,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFADFFC6D49CF8C90D80F8EF" box="[151,216,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFADFFC6D4EDF8C80C64F8EF" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[230,316,1891,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D4EDF8C80C64F8EF" box="[230,316,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">T. mesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D54FF8C90CDCF8EF" bold="true" box="[324,388,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFADFFC6D54FF8C90CDCF8EF" box="[324,388,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFADFFC6D5C8F8C80F19F8EF" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[451,577,1890,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henrardi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D5C8F8C80F19F8EF" box="[451,577,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">T. henrardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFADFFC6D642F8C90FD1F8EF" bold="true" box="[585,649,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFADFFC6D642F8C90FD1F8EF" box="[585,649,1890,1916]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by having complex retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA); large median apophysis (MA) with quadrangular-shaped anterior branch and tubular posterior one (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFADFFC6D091F82D0D99F857" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 111</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 29A–B; figs 34C–F; 36A–D; 37A–B; 38C–F; 40A–B; 42A–D; 43A–B; 44A–F; 46A–D; 47A–B; 55A–D; 56A–B), but can be distinguished by longer, thinner, apically curved anterior branch of median apophysis (aMA); retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) with bifid and wide anterior branch (aRTA), long posterior branch (pRTA), apically rounded (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D56CFF100CA1FF46" box="[359,505,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 55" captionStartId="79.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1328,196,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@79.[257,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 55. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 300µm; C–D: 500 µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520914/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Figs 55A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D60CFF110F05FF46" box="[519,605,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="80.[151,250,1639,1663]" captionTargetBox="[164,1431,194,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-27@80.[151,1436,181,1616]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURE 56. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm.Abbreviations:ApC, appendix of the conductor; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; EB, embolus base; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; pRTA, posterior branch of retrolateral apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; VTA, ventral tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520918/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">56A–B</figureCitation>
). Females are similar those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFACFFC7D7CFFF1008C0FF46" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[964,1432,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barronus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D7CFFF1009D7FF46" box="[964,1167,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tenedos barronus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFACFFC7D093FF1008C0FF46" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[1176,1432,187,213]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFACFFC7D49CFF740F50FF6A" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,520,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoeferi">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D49CFF740C5BFF6A" box="[151,259,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">T. hoeferi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFACFFC7D507FF740F50FF6A" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[268,520,223,249]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFACFFC7D64EFF740940FF6A" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[581,1048,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrangulatus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D64EFF740E4BFF6A" box="[581,787,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">T. quadrangulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFACFFC7D717FF740940FF6A" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[796,1048,223,249]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by long seminal receptacles (SR) curved towards median septum of epigyne (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFACFFC7D6B8FEA80E8FFE8E" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[691,983,259,285]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 87</bibRefCitation>
, 100, 116, figs 10C–D, 18D–E, 33A–B; figs 12E–F; 13C–D; 55E–F; 56C–D), but are characterized by elongated atrium (A) and tongue-shaped median field plate (MFP) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D525FEE00CEDFEF6" box="[302,437,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 55" captionStartId="79.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1328,196,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@79.[257,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 55. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 300µm; C–D: 500 µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520914/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Figs 55E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D5CBFEE10F4EFEF6" box="[448,534,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="80.[151,250,1639,1663]" captionTargetBox="[164,1431,194,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-27@80.[151,1436,181,1616]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURE 56. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm.Abbreviations:ApC, appendix of the conductor; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; EB, embolus base; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; pRTA, posterior branch of retrolateral apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; VTA, ventral tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520918/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">56C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFFACFFC7D4CCFEC50DA1F9BE" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFACFFC7D4CCFEC50EDAFBCA" blockId="81.[151,1437,151,1618]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D4CCFEC50C01FE1B" bold="true" box="[199,345,366,392]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D568FEC40CC5FE1A" box="[355,413,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Male</emphasis>
(IAvH-I-3731). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D6EDFEC40E2BFE1A" box="[742,883,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 54" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,453,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-94@78.[151,1437,453,1840]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 54. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-3731): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (IAvH-I-3441): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520910/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Fig. 54A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace dark brown. Chelicerae with paturon base dark brown, apically brown, fangs brown-reddish. Endites brown, white on anterior region. Labium and sternum brown. Legs: coxae-tarsi I–IV light brown with dark patches. Abdomen: dorsally dark gray with eight white guanine spots organized as follows: two large and rounded spots, anteriorly positioned; two irregular and elongated spots smaller than anterior ones, on posteromedial position; two irregular spots larger than anterior ones and with an anterior notch, medially positioned; two transversal spots partially fused in median region, posteriorly positioned. Laterally dark gray with a wide oblique band. Ventrally covered by a large spot. Spinnerets light brown. Measurements: total length 4.62, carapace length 2.51, width 1.71, height 1.08. Clypeus height 0.51. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.09, ALE 0.10, PME 0.12, PLE 0.14; AME–AME 0.18, AME–ALE 0.23, AME–PME 0.25, PME–PME 0.25, PME–PLE 0.34, ALE–PLE 0.28. Chelicerae 0.58 length. Sternum length 0.94, width 0.84. Legs: I—femur 1.54/ patella 0.65/ tibia 1.51/ metatarsus 1.58/ tarsus 0.96/ total 6.24; II—1.39/ 0.58/ 1.09/ 1.13/ 0.69/ 4.88; III—1.43/ 0.57/ 0.93/ 1.23/ 0.81/ 4.97; IV—1.55/ 0.66/ 1.45/ 2.08/ 0.84/ 6.58. Abdomen length 2.09. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): II—metatarsus v1r-1r-2 (1r-1-1r-2); III—tibia v2-2-2; IV—tibia v2-2-2. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (RPC) thin, wide at base; tegulum (T) sub-rounded, almost as wide as long; subtegulum (St) almost as long as wide in ventral view, with rounded external edge; conductor (C) moderately developed, with long, strongly sclerotized region on distal side; appendix (ApC) long, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, wide at base, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (EB) approximately as wide as basal tegular membrane; basal tegular membrane (BTM) very short and flattened ending as a short tip; spermatic ducts (SD) both folds full open; ventral tibial apophysis (VTA) large, tubular, curved; median apophysis (MA) bifid, with rectangular anterior branch (aMA), posterior branch (pMA) very short, tubular; retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) large, complex with bifid anterior branch (aRTA) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D68DFB940E4DFBCA" box="[646,789,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 55" captionStartId="79.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1328,196,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@79.[257,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 55. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 300µm; C–D: 500 µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520914/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Figs 55A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D72BFB950E2EFBCA" box="[800,886,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="80.[151,250,1639,1663]" captionTargetBox="[164,1431,194,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-27@80.[151,1436,181,1616]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURE 56. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-3731): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3441): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm.Abbreviations:ApC, appendix of the conductor; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; EB, embolus base; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; pRTA, posterior branch of retrolateral apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; VTA, ventral tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520918/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">56A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFACFFC7D4CCFBC80DA1F9BE" blockId="81.[151,1437,151,1618]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFACFFC7D4CCFBC80C43FBEE" box="[199,283,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Female</emphasis>
(IAvH-I-3441). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFACFFC7D668FBC80FA8FBEE" box="[611,752,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 54" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,453,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-94@78.[151,1437,453,1840]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 54. Tenedos luzmarinae sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-3731): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (IAvH-I-3441): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520910/files/figure.png" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Fig. 54C–D</figureCitation>
): Coloration and abdominal spots pattern as male, carapace uniformly brown and posterior spots completely fused. Measurements: total length 5.87, carapace length 2.69, width 1.83, height 1.18. Clypeus height 0.55. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.08, ALE 0.09, PME 0.12, PLE 0.15; AME–AME 0.18, AME–ALE 0.26, AME–PME 0.24, PME–PME 0.26, PME–PLE 0.41, ALE–PLE 0.30. Chelicerae 0.79 length. Sternum length 0.94, width 0.84. Legs: I—femur 1.25/ patella 0.70/ tibia 1.33/ metatarsus 1.35/ tarsus 0.72/ total 5.35; II—1.30/ 0.62/ 0.97/ 1.03/ 0.69/ 4.61; III—1.38/ 0.69/ 0.91/ 1.16/ 0.76/ 4.90; IV—1.70/ 0.63/ 1.49/ 1.89/ 0.99/ 6.70. Abdomen length 3.19. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—tibia v2-1p-2, p0, metatarsus v1r-1r-2; II—tibia v1r-1r-2; III—metatarsus v2-0-2. Epigyne: lateral borders (LB) short, in posteromedial position, forming elongated atrium (A), rounded in anterior region; median field plate (MFP) longer than wide, rounded in basal edge; copulatory ducts (CD) very short, wide, almost undistinguished from spermathecae; seminal receptacles (SR) long, thin, curved towards median septum; spermathecae (S) large, rounded, posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts (FD) approximately as long as spermathecae length (
